  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614348944683-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614348944683-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614348944683-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614348944683-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614348944683-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614348951396-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614348951396-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614348951396-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614348951396-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614348951396-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, combine your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>honey</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>yang-nyum sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614348970453-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614348970453-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614348970453-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614348970453-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614348970453-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and shred finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Combine 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> yang-nyum sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with your <strong>mayo</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a separate bowl – this is your <strong>creamy Korean-style dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614348992307-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614348992307-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614348992307-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614348992307-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614348992307-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced chicken breast</strong> to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and your<strong> soy sauce</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up so the chicken is fully coated</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a separate bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to the bowl with the <strong>cornflour</strong> and give it a good mix up until all the chicken is coated</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614349100078-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614349100078-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614349100078-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614349100078-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614349100078-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the whole base of the pan) over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and cook for 5-6 min on each side until golden and crispy and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy chicken</strong></p><p>Once crispy, transfer to kitchen paper and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614349113251-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614349113251-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614349113251-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614349113251-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614349113251-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is done, carefully pour away the oil</p><p>Tip: Store it in a glass jar and you can use this oil again for frying!</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat and add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>yang-nyum sauce</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add the<strong> crispy chicken </strong>with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Korean-style yang-nyum fried chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614349141236-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614349141236-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614349141236-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614349141236-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614349141236-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>grated carrot</strong> and <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> – this is your <strong>salad</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>Korean-style yang-nyum fried chicken</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> and <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Garnish the chicken with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and drizzle the <strong>creamy Korean-style dressing</strong> over the salad and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
